  <script type="application/json" data-target="react-app.embeddedData">{"payload":{"codeViewRepoRoute":{"path":"/","refInfo":{"name":"main","listCacheKey":"v0:1753436760.379294","canEdit":false,"refType":"branch","currentOid":"9103547f135227870a368446d6afdc87b194bb75"},"tree":{"items":[{"name":"README.md","path":"README.md","contentType":"file"}],"totalCount":1,"templateDirectorySuggestionUrl":null,"readme":null,"showBranchInfobar":false},"userNameDisplayConfiguration":null,"treeExpanded":false,"symbolsExpanded":false,"copilotSWEAgentEnabled":false,"isOverview":true,"overview":{"banners":{"shouldRecommendReadme":false,"isPersonalRepo":false,"showUseActionBanner":false,"actionSlug":null,"actionId":null,"showProtectBranchBanner":false,"transactionalMessageBanner":null,"publishBannersInfo":{"dismissActionNoticePath":"/settings/dismiss-notice/publish_action_from_repo","releasePath":"/ElaSrbrn/Carbapenem-resistant-Enterobacterales-Plasmid-clustering-pipeline/releases/new?marketplace=true","showPublishActionBanner":false},"interactionLimitBanner":null,"showInvitationBanner":false,"inviterName":null,"actionsMigrationBannerInfo":{"releaseTags":[],"showImmutableActionsMigrationBanner":false,"initialMigrationStatus":null}},"codeButton":{"contactPath":"/contact","isEnterprise":false,"local":{"protocolInfo":{"httpAvailable":true,"sshAvailable":null,"httpUrl":"https://github.com/ElaSrbrn/Carbapenem-resistant-Enterobacterales-Plasmid-clustering-pipeline.git","showCloneWarning":null,"sshUrl":null,"sshCertificatesRequired":null,"sshCertificatesAvailable":null,"ghCliUrl":"gh repo clone ElaSrbrn/Carbapenem-resistant-Enterobacterales-Plasmid-clustering-pipeline","defaultProtocol":"http","newSshKeyUrl":"/settings/ssh/new","setProtocolPath":"/users/set_protocol"},"platformInfo":{"cloneUrl":"https://desktop.github.com","showVisualStudioCloneButton":false,"visualStudioCloneUrl":"https://windows.github.com","showXcodeCloneButton":false,"xcodeCloneUrl":"xcode://clone?repo=https%3A%2F%2Fgithub.com%2FElaSrbrn%2FCarbapenem-resistant-Enterobacterales-Plasmid-clustering-pipeline","zipballUrl":"/ElaSrbrn/Carbapenem-resistant-Enterobacterales-Plasmid-clustering-pipeline/archive/refs/heads/main.zip"}},"newCodespacePath":"/codespaces/new?hide_repo_select=true\u0026repo=1026093388"},"popovers":{"rename":null,"renamedParentRepo":null},"commitCount":"16","overviewFiles":[{"displayName":"README.md","repoName":"Carbapenem-resistant-Enterobacterales-Plasmid-clustering-pipeline","refName":"main","path":"README.md","preferredFileType":"readme","tabName":"README","richText":"\u003carticle class=\"markdown-body entry-content container-lg\" itemprop=\"text\"\u003e\u003cdiv class=\"markdown-heading\" dir=\"auto\"\u003e\u003ch1 tabindex=\"-1\" class=\"heading-element\" dir=\"auto\"\u003eCarbapenem-resistant Enterobacterales: Plasmid-clustering pipeline\u003c/h1\u003e\u003ca id=\"user-content-carbapenem-resistant-enterobacterales-plasmid-clustering-pipeline\" class=\"anchor\" aria-label=\"Permalink: Carbapenem-resistant Enterobacterales: Plasmid-clustering pipeline\" href=\"#carbapenem-resistant-enterobacterales-plasmid-clustering-pipeline\"\u003e\u003csvg class=\"octicon octicon-link\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" version=\"1.1\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\u003e\u003cpath d=\"m7.775 3.275 1.25-1.25a3.5 3.5 0 1 1 4.95 4.95l-2.5 2.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1-4.95 0 .751.751 0 0 1 .018-1.042.751.751 0 0 1 1.042-.018 1.998 1.998 0 0 0 2.83 0l2.5-2.5a2.002 2.002 0 0 0-2.83-2.83l-1.25 1.25a.751.751 0 0 1-1.042-.018.751.751 0 0 1-.018-1.042Zm-4.69 9.64a1.998 1.998 0 0 0 2.83 0l1.25-1.25a.751.751 0 0 1 1.042.018.751.751 0 0 1 .018 1.042l-1.25 1.25a3.5 3.5 0 1 1-4.95-4.95l2.5-2.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1 4.95 0 .751.751 0 0 1-.018 1.042.751.751 0 0 1-1.042.018 1.998 1.998 0 0 0-2.83 0l-2.5 2.5a1.998 1.998 0 0 0 0 2.83Z\"\u003e\u003c/path\u003e\u003c/svg\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cp dir=\"auto\"\u003eThis repository offers description of the analytical steps needed for plasmid-encoded resistance dynamics investigation using Oxford Nanopore reads. This README outlines what to do and which tools to use. There are also automated softwares that provide similar analyses for non-experts, but the tools and parameters that they use are usually not fully visible. This pipeline was used in the study xxx and the study sequences are available in the National Center for Biotechnology Information (NCBI) under BioProject accession number PRJNA1297122.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003chr\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"markdown-heading\" dir=\"auto\"\u003e\u003ch2 tabindex=\"-1\" class=\"heading-element\" dir=\"auto\"\u003e1. Goal \u0026amp; Scope\u003c/h2\u003e\u003ca id=\"user-content-1-goal--scope\" class=\"anchor\" aria-label=\"Permalink: 1. Goal \u0026amp; Scope\" href=\"#1-goal--scope\"\u003e\u003csvg class=\"octicon octicon-link\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" version=\"1.1\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\u003e\u003cpath d=\"m7.775 3.275 1.25-1.25a3.5 3.5 0 1 1 4.95 4.95l-2.5 2.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1-4.95 0 .751.751 0 0 1 .018-1.042.751.751 0 0 1 1.042-.018 1.998 1.998 0 0 0 2.83 0l2.5-2.5a2.002 2.002 0 0 0-2.83-2.83l-1.25 1.25a.751.751 0 0 1-1.042-.018.751.751 0 0 1-.018-1.042Zm-4.69 9.64a1.998 1.998 0 0 0 2.83 0l1.25-1.25a.751.751 0 0 1 1.042.018.751.751 0 0 1 .018 1.042l-1.25 1.25a3.5 3.5 0 1 1-4.95-4.95l2.5-2.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1 4.95 0 .751.751 0 0 1-.018 1.042.751.751 0 0 1-1.042.018 1.998 1.998 0 0 0-2.83 0l-2.5 2.5a1.998 1.998 0 0 0 0 2.83Z\"\u003e\u003c/path\u003e\u003c/svg\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cp dir=\"auto\"\u003eIdentify and compare plasmids (and chromosomes) from relevant bacterial isolates sequenced with the RBK114 library preparation kit on a R10.4.1 MinION flowcell:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul dir=\"auto\"\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eReconstruct plasmids and annotate resistance/replicon markers\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eAssess plasmid and chromosomal relatedness (SNP distances, plasmid clustering)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003chr\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"markdown-heading\" dir=\"auto\"\u003e\u003ch2 tabindex=\"-1\" class=\"heading-element\" dir=\"auto\"\u003e2. Workflow Overview\u003c/h2\u003e\u003ca id=\"user-content-2-workflow-overview\" class=\"anchor\" aria-label=\"Permalink: 2. Workflow Overview\" href=\"#2-workflow-overview\"\u003e\u003csvg class=\"octicon octicon-link\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" version=\"1.1\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\u003e\u003cpath d=\"m7.775 3.275 1.25-1.25a3.5 3.5 0 1 1 4.95 4.95l-2.5 2.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1-4.95 0 .751.751 0 0 1 .018-1.042.751.751 0 0 1 1.042-.018 1.998 1.998 0 0 0 2.83 0l2.5-2.5a2.002 2.002 0 0 0-2.83-2.83l-1.25 1.25a.751.751 0 0 1-1.042-.018.751.751 0 0 1-.018-1.042Zm-4.69 9.64a1.998 1.998 0 0 0 2.83 0l1.25-1.25a.751.751 0 0 1 1.042.018.751.751 0 0 1 .018 1.042l-1.25 1.25a3.5 3.5 0 1 1-4.95-4.95l2.5-2.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1 4.95 0 .751.751 0 0 1-.018 1.042.751.751 0 0 1-1.042.018 1.998 1.998 0 0 0-2.83 0l-2.5 2.5a1.998 1.998 0 0 0 0 2.83Z\"\u003e\u003c/path\u003e\u003c/svg\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003col dir=\"auto\"\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eSignal → Bases\u003c/strong\u003e: Basecall raw POD5 signals with Dorado\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003ePer‑sample separation\u003c/strong\u003e: Demultiplex barcoded reads (Dorado demux)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eRead cleaning\u003c/strong\u003e: Adapter trimming \u0026amp; QC filtering (\u003cem\u003eoptional if the newer dorado basecaller model handles it with the --trim adapter flag\u003c/em\u003e)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eAssembly\u003c/strong\u003e: De novo assembly (Flye)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eConsensus polishing\u003c/strong\u003e: Correct (Medaka v2.0.1 with \u003ccode\u003e--bacteria\u003c/code\u003e flag)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003ePlasmid reconstruction \u0026amp; typing\u003c/strong\u003e: MOB‑Suite (mob_recon)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eAMR gene detection\u003c/strong\u003e: AMRFinderPlus\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003ePlasmid relatedness\u003c/strong\u003e: Mash first, then cluster (e.g. DCJ distance via Pling)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eMiscellaneous\u003c/strong\u003e: Manual SNP/Mash matrices \u0026amp; visualizations; species ID via Pathogenwatch or PubMLST\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ol\u003e\n\u003chr\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"markdown-heading\" dir=\"auto\"\u003e\u003ch2 tabindex=\"-1\" class=\"heading-element\" dir=\"auto\"\u003e3. Inputs\u003c/h2\u003e\u003ca id=\"user-content-3-inputs\" class=\"anchor\" aria-label=\"Permalink: 3. Inputs\" href=\"#3-inputs\"\u003e\u003csvg class=\"octicon octicon-link\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" version=\"1.1\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\u003e\u003cpath d=\"m7.775 3.275 1.25-1.25a3.5 3.5 0 1 1 4.95 4.95l-2.5 2.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1-4.95 0 .751.751 0 0 1 .018-1.042.751.751 0 0 1 1.042-.018 1.998 1.998 0 0 0 2.83 0l2.5-2.5a2.002 2.002 0 0 0-2.83-2.83l-1.25 1.25a.751.751 0 0 1-1.042-.018.751.751 0 0 1-.018-1.042Zm-4.69 9.64a1.998 1.998 0 0 0 2.83 0l1.25-1.25a.751.751 0 0 1 1.042.018.751.751 0 0 1 .018 1.042l-1.25 1.25a3.5 3.5 0 1 1-4.95-4.95l2.5-2.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1 4.95 0 .751.751 0 0 1-.018 1.042.751.751 0 0 1-1.042.018 1.998 1.998 0 0 0-2.83 0l-2.5 2.5a1.998 1.998 0 0 0 0 2.83Z\"\u003e\u003c/path\u003e\u003c/svg\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cul dir=\"auto\"\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eRaw POD5 or basecalled FASTQ (e.g., from MinKNOW)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eBarcode list (e.g. \u003ccode\u003e01–24\u003c/code\u003e)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003chr\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"markdown-heading\" dir=\"auto\"\u003e\u003ch2 tabindex=\"-1\" class=\"heading-element\" dir=\"auto\"\u003e4. Detailed Steps \u0026amp; Codes\u003c/h2\u003e\u003ca id=\"user-content-4-detailed-steps--codes\" class=\"anchor\" aria-label=\"Permalink: 4. Detailed Steps \u0026amp; Codes\" href=\"#4-detailed-steps--codes\"\u003e\u003csvg class=\"octicon octicon-link\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" version=\"1.1\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\u003e\u003cpath d=\"m7.775 3.275 1.25-1.25a3.5 3.5 0 1 1 4.95 4.95l-2.5 2.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1-4.95 0 .751.751 0 0 1 .018-1.042.751.751 0 0 1 1.042-.018 1.998 1.998 0 0 0 2.83 0l2.5-2.5a2.002 2.002 0 0 0-2.83-2.83l-1.25 1.25a.751.751 0 0 1-1.042-.018.751.751 0 0 1-.018-1.042Zm-4.69 9.64a1.998 1.998 0 0 0 2.83 0l1.25-1.25a.751.751 0 0 1 1.042.018.751.751 0 0 1 .018 1.042l-1.25 1.25a3.5 3.5 0 1 1-4.95-4.95l2.5-2.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1 4.95 0 .751.751 0 0 1-.018 1.042.751.751 0 0 1-1.042.018 1.998 1.998 0 0 0-2.83 0l-2.5 2.5a1.998 1.998 0 0 0 0 2.83Z\"\u003e\u003c/path\u003e\u003c/svg\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cblockquote\u003e\n\u003cp dir=\"auto\"\u003eNote: Replace placeholder paths, models, parameters as appropriate. All software versions are listed below.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/blockquote\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"markdown-heading\" dir=\"auto\"\u003e\u003ch3 tabindex=\"-1\" class=\"heading-element\" dir=\"auto\"\u003e4.1 Basecalling\u003c/h3\u003e\u003ca id=\"user-content-41-basecalling\" class=\"anchor\" aria-label=\"Permalink: 4.1 Basecalling\" href=\"#41-basecalling\"\u003e\u003csvg class=\"octicon octicon-link\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" version=\"1.1\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\u003e\u003cpath d=\"m7.775 3.275 1.25-1.25a3.5 3.5 0 1 1 4.95 4.95l-2.5 2.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1-4.95 0 .751.751 0 0 1 .018-1.042.751.751 0 0 1 1.042-.018 1.998 1.998 0 0 0 2.83 0l2.5-2.5a2.002 2.002 0 0 0-2.83-2.83l-1.25 1.25a.751.751 0 0 1-1.042-.018.751.751 0 0 1-.018-1.042Zm-4.69 9.64a1.998 1.998 0 0 0 2.83 0l1.25-1.25a.751.751 0 0 1 1.042.018.751.751 0 0 1 .018 1.042l-1.25 1.25a3.5 3.5 0 1 1-4.95-4.95l2.5-2.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1 4.95 0 .751.751 0 0 1-.018 1.042.751.751 0 0 1-1.042.018 1.998 1.998 0 0 0-2.83 0l-2.5 2.5a1.998 1.998 0 0 0 0 2.83Z\"\u003e\u003c/path\u003e\u003c/svg\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cp dir=\"auto\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eTool:\u003c/strong\u003e Dorado\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"highlight highlight-source-shell notranslate position-relative overflow-auto\" dir=\"auto\" data-snippet-clipboard-copy-content=\"DORADO_BIN=\u0026quot;/path/to/dorado\u0026quot;\nCONFIG_FILE=\u0026quot;/path/to/dna_r10.4.1_e8.2_400bps_sup@v5.0.0\u0026quot;\nINPUT_DIR=\u0026quot;/path/to/pod5_dir\u0026quot;\nOUTDIR=\u0026quot;/path/to/output\u0026quot;\nKIT=\u0026quot;SQK-RBK114-24\u0026quot;\n\nmkdir -p \u0026quot;$OUTDIR\u0026quot;\n\u0026quot;$DORADO_BIN\u0026quot; basecaller \u0026quot;$CONFIG_FILE\u0026quot; \u0026quot;$INPUT_DIR\u0026quot; \\\n  --emit-fastq --kit-name \u0026quot;$KIT\u0026quot; -r --no-trim \\\n  \u0026gt; \u0026quot;$OUTDIR/basecalled.fastq\u0026quot;\"\u003e\u003cpre\u003eDORADO_BIN=\u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e/path/to/dorado\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\nCONFIG_FILE=\u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e/path/to/dna_r10.4.1_e8.2_400bps_sup@v5.0.0\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\nINPUT_DIR=\u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e/path/to/pod5_dir\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\nOUTDIR=\u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e/path/to/output\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\nKIT=\u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003eSQK-RBK114-24\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\n\nmkdir -p \u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e$OUTDIR\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\n\u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e$DORADO_BIN\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e basecaller \u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e$CONFIG_FILE\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e$INPUT_DIR\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e \\\n  --emit-fastq --kit-name \u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e$KIT\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e -r --no-trim \\\n  \u003cspan class=\"pl-k\"\u003e\u0026gt;\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e$OUTDIR\u003c/span\u003e/basecalled.fastq\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"markdown-heading\" dir=\"auto\"\u003e\u003ch3 tabindex=\"-1\" class=\"heading-element\" dir=\"auto\"\u003e4.2 Demultiplexing\u003c/h3\u003e\u003ca id=\"user-content-42-demultiplexing\" class=\"anchor\" aria-label=\"Permalink: 4.2 Demultiplexing\" href=\"#42-demultiplexing\"\u003e\u003csvg class=\"octicon octicon-link\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" version=\"1.1\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\u003e\u003cpath d=\"m7.775 3.275 1.25-1.25a3.5 3.5 0 1 1 4.95 4.95l-2.5 2.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1-4.95 0 .751.751 0 0 1 .018-1.042.751.751 0 0 1 1.042-.018 1.998 1.998 0 0 0 2.83 0l2.5-2.5a2.002 2.002 0 0 0-2.83-2.83l-1.25 1.25a.751.751 0 0 1-1.042-.018.751.751 0 0 1-.018-1.042Zm-4.69 9.64a1.998 1.998 0 0 0 2.83 0l1.25-1.25a.751.751 0 0 1 1.042.018.751.751 0 0 1 .018 1.042l-1.25 1.25a3.5 3.5 0 1 1-4.95-4.95l2.5-2.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1 4.95 0 .751.751 0 0 1-.018 1.042.751.751 0 0 1-1.042.018 1.998 1.998 0 0 0-2.83 0l-2.5 2.5a1.998 1.998 0 0 0 0 2.83Z\"\u003e\u003c/path\u003e\u003c/svg\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cp dir=\"auto\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eTool:\u003c/strong\u003e Dorado demux\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"highlight highlight-source-shell notranslate position-relative overflow-auto\" dir=\"auto\" data-snippet-clipboard-copy-content=\"\u0026quot;$DORADO_BIN\u0026quot; demux \\\n  --output-dir \u0026quot;$OUTDIR/demux\u0026quot; \\\n  --emit-fastq --kit-name \u0026quot;$KIT\u0026quot; \\\n  \u0026quot;$OUTDIR/basecalled.fastq\u0026quot;\n# yields files like demux/barcode01.fastq\"\u003e\u003cpre\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e$DORADO_BIN\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e demux \\\n  --output-dir \u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e$OUTDIR\u003c/span\u003e/demux\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e \\\n  --emit-fastq --kit-name \u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e$KIT\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e \\\n  \u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e$OUTDIR\u003c/span\u003e/basecalled.fastq\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\n\u003cspan class=\"pl-c\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-c\"\u003e#\u003c/span\u003e yields files like demux/barcode01.fastq\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"markdown-heading\" dir=\"auto\"\u003e\u003ch3 tabindex=\"-1\" class=\"heading-element\" dir=\"auto\"\u003e4.3 Trimming \u0026amp; Filtering\u003c/h3\u003e\u003ca id=\"user-content-43-trimming--filtering\" class=\"anchor\" aria-label=\"Permalink: 4.3 Trimming \u0026amp; Filtering\" href=\"#43-trimming--filtering\"\u003e\u003csvg class=\"octicon octicon-link\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" version=\"1.1\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\u003e\u003cpath d=\"m7.775 3.275 1.25-1.25a3.5 3.5 0 1 1 4.95 4.95l-2.5 2.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1-4.95 0 .751.751 0 0 1 .018-1.042.751.751 0 0 1 1.042-.018 1.998 1.998 0 0 0 2.83 0l2.5-2.5a2.002 2.002 0 0 0-2.83-2.83l-1.25 1.25a.751.751 0 0 1-1.042-.018.751.751 0 0 1-.018-1.042Zm-4.69 9.64a1.998 1.998 0 0 0 2.83 0l1.25-1.25a.751.751 0 0 1 1.042.018.751.751 0 0 1 .018 1.042l-1.25 1.25a3.5 3.5 0 1 1-4.95-4.95l2.5-2.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1 4.95 0 .751.751 0 0 1-.018 1.042.751.751 0 0 1-1.042.018 1.998 1.998 0 0 0-2.83 0l-2.5 2.5a1.998 1.998 0 0 0 0 2.83Z\"\u003e\u003c/path\u003e\u003c/svg\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cp dir=\"auto\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eTools:\u003c/strong\u003e Porechop, NanoFilt, Seqkit\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"highlight highlight-source-shell notranslate position-relative overflow-auto\" dir=\"auto\" data-snippet-clipboard-copy-content=\"BCLIST=$(seq -w 01 24)\nRAW_PREFIX=\u0026quot;$OUTDIR/demux/barcode\u0026quot;\nPC_DIR=\u0026quot;$OUTDIR/porechop\u0026quot;\nNF_DIR=\u0026quot;$OUTDIR/filtered_reads\u0026quot;\nSTATS_DIR=\u0026quot;$OUTDIR/stats\u0026quot;\nQMIN=8; LMIN=200\nmkdir -p \u0026quot;$PC_DIR\u0026quot; \u0026quot;$NF_DIR\u0026quot; \u0026quot;$STATS_DIR\u0026quot;\n\nfor bc in $BCLIST; do\n  in=\u0026quot;${RAW_PREFIX}${bc}.fastq\u0026quot;; [[ -s \u0026quot;$in\u0026quot; ]] || continue\n  trim=\u0026quot;$PC_DIR/trimmed_${bc}.fastq\u0026quot;\n  out=\u0026quot;$NF_DIR/filtered_barcode${bc}.fastq\u0026quot;\n  porechop -i \u0026quot;$in\u0026quot; -o \u0026quot;$trim\u0026quot;\n  NanoFilt -q \u0026quot;$QMIN\u0026quot; -l \u0026quot;$LMIN\u0026quot; \u0026lt; \u0026quot;$trim\u0026quot; \u0026gt; \u0026quot;$out\u0026quot;\n  rm -f \u0026quot;$trim\u0026quot;\ndone\n\nfor fq in \u0026quot;$NF_DIR\u0026quot;/*.fastq; do\n  [[ -e \u0026quot;$fq\u0026quot; ]] || continue\n  seqkit stats -T -a \u0026quot;$fq\u0026quot; \u0026gt; \u0026quot;$STATS_DIR/$(basename \u0026quot;${fq%.fastq}\u0026quot;).txt\u0026quot;\ndone\"\u003e\u003cpre\u003eBCLIST=\u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e$(\u003c/span\u003eseq -w 01 24\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e)\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\nRAW_PREFIX=\u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e$OUTDIR\u003c/span\u003e/demux/barcode\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\nPC_DIR=\u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e$OUTDIR\u003c/span\u003e/porechop\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\nNF_DIR=\u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e$OUTDIR\u003c/span\u003e/filtered_reads\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\nSTATS_DIR=\u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e$OUTDIR\u003c/span\u003e/stats\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\nQMIN=8\u003cspan class=\"pl-k\"\u003e;\u003c/span\u003e LMIN=200\nmkdir -p \u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e$PC_DIR\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e$NF_DIR\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e$STATS_DIR\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\n\n\u003cspan class=\"pl-k\"\u003efor\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003ebc\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"pl-k\"\u003ein\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e$BCLIST\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-k\"\u003e;\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"pl-k\"\u003edo\u003c/span\u003e\n  in=\u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e${RAW_PREFIX}${bc}\u003c/span\u003e.fastq\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-k\"\u003e;\u003c/span\u003e [[ \u003cspan class=\"pl-k\"\u003e-s\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e$in\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e ]] \u003cspan class=\"pl-k\"\u003e||\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"pl-k\"\u003econtinue\u003c/span\u003e\n  trim=\u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e$PC_DIR\u003c/span\u003e/trimmed_\u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e${bc}\u003c/span\u003e.fastq\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\n  out=\u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e$NF_DIR\u003c/span\u003e/filtered_barcode\u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e${bc}\u003c/span\u003e.fastq\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\n  porechop -i \u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e$in\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e -o \u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e$trim\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\n  NanoFilt -q \u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e$QMIN\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e -l \u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e$LMIN\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"pl-k\"\u003e\u0026lt;\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e$trim\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"pl-k\"\u003e\u0026gt;\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e$out\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\n  rm -f \u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e$trim\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\n\u003cspan class=\"pl-k\"\u003edone\u003c/span\u003e\n\n\u003cspan class=\"pl-k\"\u003efor\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003efq\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"pl-k\"\u003ein\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e$NF_DIR\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e/\u003cspan class=\"pl-k\"\u003e*\u003c/span\u003e.fastq\u003cspan class=\"pl-k\"\u003e;\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"pl-k\"\u003edo\u003c/span\u003e\n  [[ \u003cspan class=\"pl-k\"\u003e-e\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e$fq\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e ]] \u003cspan class=\"pl-k\"\u003e||\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"pl-k\"\u003econtinue\u003c/span\u003e\n  seqkit stats -T -a \u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e$fq\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"pl-k\"\u003e\u0026gt;\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e$STATS_DIR\u003c/span\u003e/\u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e$(\u003c/span\u003ebasename \u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e${fq\u003cspan class=\"pl-k\"\u003e%\u003c/span\u003e.fastq}\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e)\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e.txt\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\n\u003cspan class=\"pl-k\"\u003edone\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cp dir=\"auto\"\u003eNotes:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul dir=\"auto\"\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eIf you used multiple barcodes for the same sample and concatenated the reads you need to be careful with duplicated read IDs, as that might impair Flye from assembling properly. Thus, make sure to remove any duplicated reads before moving on to the assembly step.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eIn case you want to read quality metric outputs, you could try seqkit (see here: \u003ca href=\"https://github.com/shenwei356/seqkit\"\u003ehttps://github.com/shenwei356/seqkit\u003c/a\u003e for more information). Alternatively, newer dorado basecalling models offer a summary of basecalled data quality metrics.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"markdown-heading\" dir=\"auto\"\u003e\u003ch3 tabindex=\"-1\" class=\"heading-element\" dir=\"auto\"\u003e4.4 Assembly\u003c/h3\u003e\u003ca id=\"user-content-44-assembly\" class=\"anchor\" aria-label=\"Permalink: 4.4 Assembly\" href=\"#44-assembly\"\u003e\u003csvg class=\"octicon octicon-link\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" version=\"1.1\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\u003e\u003cpath d=\"m7.775 3.275 1.25-1.25a3.5 3.5 0 1 1 4.95 4.95l-2.5 2.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1-4.95 0 .751.751 0 0 1 .018-1.042.751.751 0 0 1 1.042-.018 1.998 1.998 0 0 0 2.83 0l2.5-2.5a2.002 2.002 0 0 0-2.83-2.83l-1.25 1.25a.751.751 0 0 1-1.042-.018.751.751 0 0 1-.018-1.042Zm-4.69 9.64a1.998 1.998 0 0 0 2.83 0l1.25-1.25a.751.751 0 0 1 1.042.018.751.751 0 0 1 .018 1.042l-1.25 1.25a3.5 3.5 0 1 1-4.95-4.95l2.5-2.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1 4.95 0 .751.751 0 0 1-.018 1.042.751.751 0 0 1-1.042.018 1.998 1.998 0 0 0-2.83 0l-2.5 2.5a1.998 1.998 0 0 0 0 2.83Z\"\u003e\u003c/path\u003e\u003c/svg\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cp dir=\"auto\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eTool:\u003c/strong\u003e Flye\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"highlight highlight-source-shell notranslate position-relative overflow-auto\" dir=\"auto\" data-snippet-clipboard-copy-content=\"GENOME_SIZE=\u0026quot;5m\u0026quot;; THREADS=8\nFLY_DIR=\u0026quot;$OUTDIR/flye\u0026quot;; mkdir -p \u0026quot;$FLY_DIR\u0026quot;\nfor bc in $BCLIST; do\n  reads=\u0026quot;$NF_DIR/filtered_barcode${bc}.fastq\u0026quot;; [[ -s \u0026quot;$reads\u0026quot; ]] || continue\n  flye --nano-hq \u0026quot;$reads\u0026quot; --out-dir \u0026quot;$FLY_DIR/barcode${bc}\u0026quot; \\\n       --genome-size \u0026quot;$GENOME_SIZE\u0026quot; --threads \u0026quot;$THREADS\u0026quot;\ndone\"\u003e\u003cpre\u003eGENOME_SIZE=\u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e5m\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-k\"\u003e;\u003c/span\u003e THREADS=8\nFLY_DIR=\u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e$OUTDIR\u003c/span\u003e/flye\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-k\"\u003e;\u003c/span\u003e mkdir -p \u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e$FLY_DIR\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\n\u003cspan class=\"pl-k\"\u003efor\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003ebc\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"pl-k\"\u003ein\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e$BCLIST\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-k\"\u003e;\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"pl-k\"\u003edo\u003c/span\u003e\n  reads=\u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e$NF_DIR\u003c/span\u003e/filtered_barcode\u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e${bc}\u003c/span\u003e.fastq\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-k\"\u003e;\u003c/span\u003e [[ \u003cspan class=\"pl-k\"\u003e-s\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e$reads\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e ]] \u003cspan class=\"pl-k\"\u003e||\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"pl-k\"\u003econtinue\u003c/span\u003e\n  flye --nano-hq \u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e$reads\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e --out-dir \u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e$FLY_DIR\u003c/span\u003e/barcode\u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e${bc}\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e \\\n       --genome-size \u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e$GENOME_SIZE\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e --threads \u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e$THREADS\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\n\u003cspan class=\"pl-k\"\u003edone\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cp dir=\"auto\"\u003eNote: I added the genome size, however for newer versions of Flye this might not be necessary anymore.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"markdown-heading\" dir=\"auto\"\u003e\u003ch3 tabindex=\"-1\" class=\"heading-element\" dir=\"auto\"\u003e4.5 Depth estimation and Polishing\u003c/h3\u003e\u003ca id=\"user-content-45-depth-estimation-and-polishing\" class=\"anchor\" aria-label=\"Permalink: 4.5 Depth estimation and Polishing\" href=\"#45-depth-estimation-and-polishing\"\u003e\u003csvg class=\"octicon octicon-link\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" version=\"1.1\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\u003e\u003cpath d=\"m7.775 3.275 1.25-1.25a3.5 3.5 0 1 1 4.95 4.95l-2.5 2.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1-4.95 0 .751.751 0 0 1 .018-1.042.751.751 0 0 1 1.042-.018 1.998 1.998 0 0 0 2.83 0l2.5-2.5a2.002 2.002 0 0 0-2.83-2.83l-1.25 1.25a.751.751 0 0 1-1.042-.018.751.751 0 0 1-.018-1.042Zm-4.69 9.64a1.998 1.998 0 0 0 2.83 0l1.25-1.25a.751.751 0 0 1 1.042.018.751.751 0 0 1 .018 1.042l-1.25 1.25a3.5 3.5 0 1 1-4.95-4.95l2.5-2.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1 4.95 0 .751.751 0 0 1-.018 1.042.751.751 0 0 1-1.042.018 1.998 1.998 0 0 0-2.83 0l-2.5 2.5a1.998 1.998 0 0 0 0 2.83Z\"\u003e\u003c/path\u003e\u003c/svg\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cp dir=\"auto\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eTools:\u003c/strong\u003e Minimap2, Samtools, Medaka v2.0.1 (\u003ccode\u003e--bacteria\u003c/code\u003e)\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"highlight highlight-source-shell notranslate position-relative overflow-auto\" dir=\"auto\" data-snippet-clipboard-copy-content=\"MIN_DIR=\u0026quot;$OUTDIR/minimap\u0026quot;\nMEDAKA_DIR=\u0026quot;$OUTDIR/medaka\u0026quot;\nmkdir -p \u0026quot;$MIN_DIR\u0026quot; \u0026quot;$MEDAKA_DIR\u0026quot;\n\nTHREADS=8\n\nfor bc in $BCLIST; do\n  asm=\u0026quot;$FLY_DIR/barcode${bc}/assembly.fasta\u0026quot;\n  reads=\u0026quot;$NF_DIR/filtered_barcode${bc}.fastq\u0026quot;\n  med_out=\u0026quot;$MEDAKA_DIR/barcode${bc}\u0026quot;\n\n  mkdir -p \u0026quot;$med_out\u0026quot;\n\n  medaka_consensus -i \u0026quot;$reads\u0026quot; -d \u0026quot;$asm\u0026quot; -o \u0026quot;$med_out\u0026quot; \\\n    -t \u0026quot;$THREADS\u0026quot; --bacteria\ndone\n\n*Note: The --bacteria flag has been shown to improve the assembly quality and reduce the error rates of bacterial assemblies. Medaka models \u0026lt;v2 have not necessarily improved assembly quality, which meamt that polishing was not necessarily recommended previously. Thus, Medaka \u0026gt;v2 should be used. Dorado also includes polishing steps, which improve assembly quality (especially for hac basecalled data) and might replace Medaka polishing in the future, so it might be worth considering those. \n\n# Run depth estimation using minimap2 + samtools\nfor bc in $BCLIST; do\n  asm=\u0026quot;$FLY_DIR/barcode${bc}/assembly.fasta\u0026quot;\n  reads=\u0026quot;$NF_DIR/filtered_barcode${bc}.fastq\u0026quot;\n  bam=\u0026quot;$COV_DIR/barcode${bc}.bam\u0026quot;\n  depth_file=\u0026quot;$COV_DIR/depth_barcode${bc}.txt\u0026quot;\n\n  [[ -s \u0026quot;$asm\u0026quot; \u0026amp;\u0026amp; -s \u0026quot;$reads\u0026quot; ]] || { echo \u0026quot;[Coverage] Missing files for barcode $bc. Skipping.\u0026quot;; continue; }\n\n  minimap2 -ax map-ont \u0026quot;$asm\u0026quot; \u0026quot;$reads\u0026quot; -t \u0026quot;$THREADS\u0026quot; \\\n    | samtools view -b - \\\n    | samtools sort -@ \u0026quot;$THREADS\u0026quot; -o \u0026quot;$bam\u0026quot; -\n\n  samtools index \u0026quot;$bam\u0026quot;\n  samtools depth \u0026quot;$bam\u0026quot; \u0026gt; \u0026quot;$depth_file\u0026quot;\n\n  # Calculate and print average depth\n  avg=$(awk '{sum += $3} END {if (NR \u0026gt; 0) print sum/NR; else print 0}' \u0026quot;$depth_file\u0026quot;)\n  echo \u0026quot;Barcode $bc average depth: $avg\u0026quot;\ndone\"\u003e\u003cpre\u003eMIN_DIR=\u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e$OUTDIR\u003c/span\u003e/minimap\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\nMEDAKA_DIR=\u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e$OUTDIR\u003c/span\u003e/medaka\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\nmkdir -p \u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e$MIN_DIR\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e$MEDAKA_DIR\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\n\nTHREADS=8\n\n\u003cspan class=\"pl-k\"\u003efor\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003ebc\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"pl-k\"\u003ein\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e$BCLIST\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-k\"\u003e;\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"pl-k\"\u003edo\u003c/span\u003e\n  asm=\u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e$FLY_DIR\u003c/span\u003e/barcode\u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e${bc}\u003c/span\u003e/assembly.fasta\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\n  reads=\u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e$NF_DIR\u003c/span\u003e/filtered_barcode\u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e${bc}\u003c/span\u003e.fastq\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\n  med_out=\u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e$MEDAKA_DIR\u003c/span\u003e/barcode\u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e${bc}\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\n\n  mkdir -p \u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e$med_out\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\n\n  medaka_consensus -i \u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e$reads\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e -d \u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e$asm\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e -o \u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e$med_out\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e \\\n    -t \u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e$THREADS\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e --bacteria\n\u003cspan class=\"pl-k\"\u003edone\u003c/span\u003e\n\n\u003cspan class=\"pl-k\"\u003e*\u003c/span\u003eNote: The --bacteria flag has been shown to improve the assembly quality and reduce the error rates of bacterial assemblies. Medaka models \u003cspan class=\"pl-k\"\u003e\u0026lt;\u003c/span\u003ev2 have not necessarily improved assembly quality, which meamt that polishing was not necessarily recommended previously. Thus, Medaka \u003cspan class=\"pl-k\"\u003e\u0026gt;\u003c/span\u003ev2 should be used. Dorado also includes polishing steps, which improve assembly quality (especially \u003cspan class=\"pl-k\"\u003efor\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003ehac basecalled data) and might replace Medaka polishing\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"pl-k\"\u003ein\u003c/span\u003e the future, so it might be worth considering those. \n\n\u003cspan class=\"pl-c\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-c\"\u003e#\u003c/span\u003e Run depth estimation using minimap2 + samtools\u003c/span\u003e\n\u003cspan class=\"pl-k\"\u003efor\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003ebc\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"pl-k\"\u003ein\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e$BCLIST\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-k\"\u003e;\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"pl-k\"\u003edo\u003c/span\u003e\n  asm=\u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e$FLY_DIR\u003c/span\u003e/barcode\u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e${bc}\u003c/span\u003e/assembly.fasta\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\n  reads=\u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e$NF_DIR\u003c/span\u003e/filtered_barcode\u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e${bc}\u003c/span\u003e.fastq\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\n  bam=\u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e$COV_DIR\u003c/span\u003e/barcode\u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e${bc}\u003c/span\u003e.bam\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\n  depth_file=\u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e$COV_DIR\u003c/span\u003e/depth_barcode\u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e${bc}\u003c/span\u003e.txt\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\n\n  [[ \u003cspan class=\"pl-k\"\u003e-s\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e$asm\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"pl-k\"\u003e\u0026amp;\u0026amp;\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"pl-k\"\u003e-s\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e$reads\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e ]] \u003cspan class=\"pl-k\"\u003e||\u003c/span\u003e { \u003cspan class=\"pl-c1\"\u003eecho\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e[Coverage] Missing files for barcode \u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e$bc\u003c/span\u003e. Skipping.\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-k\"\u003e;\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"pl-k\"\u003econtinue\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-k\"\u003e;\u003c/span\u003e }\n\n  minimap2 -ax map-ont \u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e$asm\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e$reads\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e -t \u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e$THREADS\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e \\\n    \u003cspan class=\"pl-k\"\u003e|\u003c/span\u003e samtools view -b - \\\n    \u003cspan class=\"pl-k\"\u003e|\u003c/span\u003e samtools sort -@ \u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e$THREADS\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e -o \u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e$bam\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e -\n\n  samtools index \u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e$bam\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\n  samtools depth \u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e$bam\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"pl-k\"\u003e\u0026gt;\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e$depth_file\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\n\n  \u003cspan class=\"pl-c\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-c\"\u003e#\u003c/span\u003e Calculate and print average depth\u003c/span\u003e\n  avg=\u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e$(\u003c/span\u003eawk \u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e'\u003c/span\u003e{sum += $3} END {if (NR \u0026gt; 0) print sum/NR; else print 0}\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e'\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e$depth_file\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e)\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\n  \u003cspan class=\"pl-c1\"\u003eecho\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003eBarcode \u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e$bc\u003c/span\u003e average depth: \u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e$avg\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\n\u003cspan class=\"pl-k\"\u003edone\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"markdown-heading\" dir=\"auto\"\u003e\u003ch3 tabindex=\"-1\" class=\"heading-element\" dir=\"auto\"\u003e4.6 Plasmid Reconstruction \u0026amp; Typing\u003c/h3\u003e\u003ca id=\"user-content-46-plasmid-reconstruction--typing\" class=\"anchor\" aria-label=\"Permalink: 4.6 Plasmid Reconstruction \u0026amp; Typing\" href=\"#46-plasmid-reconstruction--typing\"\u003e\u003csvg class=\"octicon octicon-link\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" version=\"1.1\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\u003e\u003cpath d=\"m7.775 3.275 1.25-1.25a3.5 3.5 0 1 1 4.95 4.95l-2.5 2.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1-4.95 0 .751.751 0 0 1 .018-1.042.751.751 0 0 1 1.042-.018 1.998 1.998 0 0 0 2.83 0l2.5-2.5a2.002 2.002 0 0 0-2.83-2.83l-1.25 1.25a.751.751 0 0 1-1.042-.018.751.751 0 0 1-.018-1.042Zm-4.69 9.64a1.998 1.998 0 0 0 2.83 0l1.25-1.25a.751.751 0 0 1 1.042.018.751.751 0 0 1 .018 1.042l-1.25 1.25a3.5 3.5 0 1 1-4.95-4.95l2.5-2.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1 4.95 0 .751.751 0 0 1-.018 1.042.751.751 0 0 1-1.042.018 1.998 1.998 0 0 0-2.83 0l-2.5 2.5a1.998 1.998 0 0 0 0 2.83Z\"\u003e\u003c/path\u003e\u003c/svg\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cp dir=\"auto\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eTool:\u003c/strong\u003e MOB‑Suite\nRun Mob-Suite on polished assemblies.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"highlight highlight-source-shell notranslate position-relative overflow-auto\" dir=\"auto\" data-snippet-clipboard-copy-content=\"MOB_DIR=\u0026quot;$OUTDIR/mob\u0026quot;; mkdir -p \u0026quot;$MOB_DIR\u0026quot;\nfor bc in $BCLIST; do\n  cns=\u0026quot;$MEDAKA_DIR/barcode${bc}/consensus.fasta\u0026quot;; [[ -s \u0026quot;$cns\u0026quot; ]] || continue\n  mob_recon --infile \u0026quot;$cns\u0026quot; --outdir \u0026quot;$MOB_DIR/barcode${bc}\u0026quot;\ndone\"\u003e\u003cpre\u003eMOB_DIR=\u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e$OUTDIR\u003c/span\u003e/mob\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-k\"\u003e;\u003c/span\u003e mkdir -p \u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e$MOB_DIR\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\n\u003cspan class=\"pl-k\"\u003efor\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003ebc\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"pl-k\"\u003ein\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e$BCLIST\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-k\"\u003e;\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"pl-k\"\u003edo\u003c/span\u003e\n  cns=\u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e$MEDAKA_DIR\u003c/span\u003e/barcode\u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e${bc}\u003c/span\u003e/consensus.fasta\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-k\"\u003e;\u003c/span\u003e [[ \u003cspan class=\"pl-k\"\u003e-s\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e$cns\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e ]] \u003cspan class=\"pl-k\"\u003e||\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"pl-k\"\u003econtinue\u003c/span\u003e\n  mob_recon --infile \u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e$cns\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e --outdir \u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e$MOB_DIR\u003c/span\u003e/barcode\u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e${bc}\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\n\u003cspan class=\"pl-k\"\u003edone\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"markdown-heading\" dir=\"auto\"\u003e\u003ch3 tabindex=\"-1\" class=\"heading-element\" dir=\"auto\"\u003e4.7 AMR Gene Detection\u003c/h3\u003e\u003ca id=\"user-content-47-amr-gene-detection\" class=\"anchor\" aria-label=\"Permalink: 4.7 AMR Gene Detection\" href=\"#47-amr-gene-detection\"\u003e\u003csvg class=\"octicon octicon-link\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" version=\"1.1\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\u003e\u003cpath d=\"m7.775 3.275 1.25-1.25a3.5 3.5 0 1 1 4.95 4.95l-2.5 2.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1-4.95 0 .751.751 0 0 1 .018-1.042.751.751 0 0 1 1.042-.018 1.998 1.998 0 0 0 2.83 0l2.5-2.5a2.002 2.002 0 0 0-2.83-2.83l-1.25 1.25a.751.751 0 0 1-1.042-.018.751.751 0 0 1-.018-1.042Zm-4.69 9.64a1.998 1.998 0 0 0 2.83 0l1.25-1.25a.751.751 0 0 1 1.042.018.751.751 0 0 1 .018 1.042l-1.25 1.25a3.5 3.5 0 1 1-4.95-4.95l2.5-2.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1 4.95 0 .751.751 0 0 1-.018 1.042.751.751 0 0 1-1.042.018 1.998 1.998 0 0 0-2.83 0l-2.5 2.5a1.998 1.998 0 0 0 0 2.83Z\"\u003e\u003c/path\u003e\u003c/svg\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cp dir=\"auto\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eTool:\u003c/strong\u003e AMRFinderPlus\nRun AMRFinderPlus on polished assemblies.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"highlight highlight-source-shell notranslate position-relative overflow-auto\" dir=\"auto\" data-snippet-clipboard-copy-content=\"AMR_DIR=\u0026quot;$OUTDIR/amr\u0026quot;; mkdir -p \u0026quot;$AMR_DIR\u0026quot;\nfor bc in $BCLIST; do\n  cns=\u0026quot;$MEDAKA_DIR/barcode${bc}/consensus.fasta\u0026quot;; [[ -s \u0026quot;$cns\u0026quot; ]] || continue\n  amrfinder -n \u0026quot;$cns\u0026quot; -o \u0026quot;$AMR_DIR/barcode${bc}.amr.txt\u0026quot; \\\n    --threads \u0026quot;$THREADS\u0026quot; --plus\ndone\"\u003e\u003cpre\u003eAMR_DIR=\u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e$OUTDIR\u003c/span\u003e/amr\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-k\"\u003e;\u003c/span\u003e mkdir -p \u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e$AMR_DIR\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\n\u003cspan class=\"pl-k\"\u003efor\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003ebc\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"pl-k\"\u003ein\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e$BCLIST\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-k\"\u003e;\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"pl-k\"\u003edo\u003c/span\u003e\n  cns=\u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e$MEDAKA_DIR\u003c/span\u003e/barcode\u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e${bc}\u003c/span\u003e/consensus.fasta\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-k\"\u003e;\u003c/span\u003e [[ \u003cspan class=\"pl-k\"\u003e-s\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e$cns\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e ]] \u003cspan class=\"pl-k\"\u003e||\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"pl-k\"\u003econtinue\u003c/span\u003e\n  amrfinder -n \u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e$cns\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e -o \u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e$AMR_DIR\u003c/span\u003e/barcode\u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e${bc}\u003c/span\u003e.amr.txt\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e \\\n    --threads \u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e$THREADS\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e --plus\n\u003cspan class=\"pl-k\"\u003edone\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"markdown-heading\" dir=\"auto\"\u003e\u003ch3 tabindex=\"-1\" class=\"heading-element\" dir=\"auto\"\u003e4.8 Chromosomal SNP Analysis\u003c/h3\u003e\u003ca id=\"user-content-48-chromosomal-snp-analysis\" class=\"anchor\" aria-label=\"Permalink: 4.8 Chromosomal SNP Analysis\" href=\"#48-chromosomal-snp-analysis\"\u003e\u003csvg class=\"octicon octicon-link\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" version=\"1.1\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\u003e\u003cpath d=\"m7.775 3.275 1.25-1.25a3.5 3.5 0 1 1 4.95 4.95l-2.5 2.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1-4.95 0 .751.751 0 0 1 .018-1.042.751.751 0 0 1 1.042-.018 1.998 1.998 0 0 0 2.83 0l2.5-2.5a2.002 2.002 0 0 0-2.83-2.83l-1.25 1.25a.751.751 0 0 1-1.042-.018.751.751 0 0 1-.018-1.042Zm-4.69 9.64a1.998 1.998 0 0 0 2.83 0l1.25-1.25a.751.751 0 0 1 1.042.018.751.751 0 0 1 .018 1.042l-1.25 1.25a3.5 3.5 0 1 1-4.95-4.95l2.5-2.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1 4.95 0 .751.751 0 0 1-.018 1.042.751.751 0 0 1-1.042.018 1.998 1.998 0 0 0-2.83 0l-2.5 2.5a1.998 1.998 0 0 0 0 2.83Z\"\u003e\u003c/path\u003e\u003c/svg\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cp dir=\"auto\"\u003eFor more detailed information please refer to the methods section in our preprint cited above.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"markdown-heading\" dir=\"auto\"\u003e\u003ch3 tabindex=\"-1\" class=\"heading-element\" dir=\"auto\"\u003e4.9 Plasmid Clustering / Distances\u003c/h3\u003e\u003ca id=\"user-content-49-plasmid-clustering--distances\" class=\"anchor\" aria-label=\"Permalink: 4.9 Plasmid Clustering / Distances\" href=\"#49-plasmid-clustering--distances\"\u003e\u003csvg class=\"octicon octicon-link\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" version=\"1.1\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\u003e\u003cpath d=\"m7.775 3.275 1.25-1.25a3.5 3.5 0 1 1 4.95 4.95l-2.5 2.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1-4.95 0 .751.751 0 0 1 .018-1.042.751.751 0 0 1 1.042-.018 1.998 1.998 0 0 0 2.83 0l2.5-2.5a2.002 2.002 0 0 0-2.83-2.83l-1.25 1.25a.751.751 0 0 1-1.042-.018.751.751 0 0 1-.018-1.042Zm-4.69 9.64a1.998 1.998 0 0 0 2.83 0l1.25-1.25a.751.751 0 0 1 1.042.018.751.751 0 0 1 .018 1.042l-1.25 1.25a3.5 3.5 0 1 1-4.95-4.95l2.5-2.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1 4.95 0 .751.751 0 0 1-.018 1.042.751.751 0 0 1-1.042.018 1.998 1.998 0 0 0-2.83 0l-2.5 2.5a1.998 1.998 0 0 0 0 2.83Z\"\u003e\u003c/path\u003e\u003c/svg\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cp dir=\"auto\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eTools:\u003c/strong\u003e Mash, Pling\nRun Mash and Pling on polished plasmid assemblies of interest (e.g., IncN, IncL/M) etc.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"highlight highlight-source-shell notranslate position-relative overflow-auto\" dir=\"auto\" data-snippet-clipboard-copy-content=\"# 1) Compute Mash distances\nPLASMID_TYPE=\u0026quot;IncN\u0026quot;\nOUT_TXT=\u0026quot;$OUTDIR/clustering/mash_${PLASMID_TYPE}.txt\u0026quot;; \u0026gt; \u0026quot;$OUT_TXT\u0026quot;\nfor i in {1..24}; do\n  for j in {1..24}; do\n    [[ $i -lt $j ]] || continue\n    f1=$(printf \u0026quot;plasmid_%s_barcode%02d.fasta\u0026quot; \u0026quot;$PLASMID_TYPE\u0026quot; \u0026quot;$i\u0026quot;)\n    f2=$(printf \u0026quot;plasmid_%s_barcode%02d.fasta\u0026quot; \u0026quot;$PLASMID_TYPE\u0026quot; \u0026quot;$j\u0026quot;)\n    [[ -f \u0026quot;$f1\u0026quot; \u0026amp;\u0026amp; -f \u0026quot;$f2\u0026quot; ]] \u0026amp;\u0026amp; mash dist \u0026quot;$f1\u0026quot; \u0026quot;$f2\u0026quot; \u0026gt;\u0026gt; \u0026quot;$OUT_TXT\u0026quot; \\\n      || echo \u0026quot;Missing: $f1 or $f2\u0026quot;\n  done\n\ndone\n\n# 2) DCJ-based clustering with Pling (after selecting pairs below threshold)\npling align --containment_distance 0.3 --cores 8 --sourmash plasmid.txt \u0026quot;$OUTDIR/clustering/pling_out\u0026quot;\n\n\n### 4.10 Miscellaneous \u0026amp; Reporting\n\n- SNP/Mash distance matrices and visualizations were done manually\n- In general, I have had good experience with bandage (cited in the preprint) to get assembly visualisations and ProkSee for visualisation of functional annotations.\n- Be careful when re-running assemblies and matching contigs previously annotated with MOB-Suite to the new assemblies (i.e., with regards to contig length etc.), as flye might change the contig-numbering when re-running again\n- Species identification was conducted externally via Pathogenwatch and/or PubMLST (see corresponding publication)\n\n---\n\n## 5. Suggested Folder Structure\n\n```text\nproject/\n├─ raw/                     # POD5/FAST5 or raw FASTQs\n├─ demux/\n├─ filtered_reads/          # post-trim/filter\n├─ flye/                    # raw assemblies\n├─ medaka/                  # polished assemblies\n├─ mob/                     # plasmid reconstruction\n├─ amr/                     # AMR gene tables\n├─ clustering/             # plasmid clustering \u0026amp; distances\n└─ reports/                 # summary tables \u0026amp; figures\"\u003e\u003cpre\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-c\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-c\"\u003e#\u003c/span\u003e 1) Compute Mash distances\u003c/span\u003e\nPLASMID_TYPE=\u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003eIncN\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\nOUT_TXT=\u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e$OUTDIR\u003c/span\u003e/clustering/mash_\u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e${PLASMID_TYPE}\u003c/span\u003e.txt\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-k\"\u003e;\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"pl-k\"\u003e\u0026gt;\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e$OUT_TXT\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\n\u003cspan class=\"pl-k\"\u003efor\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003ei\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"pl-k\"\u003ein\u003c/span\u003e {1..24}\u003cspan class=\"pl-k\"\u003e;\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"pl-k\"\u003edo\u003c/span\u003e\n  \u003cspan class=\"pl-k\"\u003efor\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003ej\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"pl-k\"\u003ein\u003c/span\u003e {1..24}\u003cspan class=\"pl-k\"\u003e;\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"pl-k\"\u003edo\u003c/span\u003e\n    [[ \u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e$i\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"pl-k\"\u003e-lt\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e$j\u003c/span\u003e ]] \u003cspan class=\"pl-k\"\u003e||\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"pl-k\"\u003econtinue\u003c/span\u003e\n    f1=\u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e$(\u003c/span\u003eprintf \u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003eplasmid_%s_barcode%02d.fasta\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e$PLASMID_TYPE\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e$i\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e)\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\n    f2=\u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e$(\u003c/span\u003eprintf \u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003eplasmid_%s_barcode%02d.fasta\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e$PLASMID_TYPE\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e$j\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e)\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\n    [[ \u003cspan class=\"pl-k\"\u003e-f\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e$f1\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"pl-k\"\u003e\u0026amp;\u0026amp;\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"pl-k\"\u003e-f\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e$f2\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e ]] \u003cspan class=\"pl-k\"\u003e\u0026amp;\u0026amp;\u003c/span\u003e mash dist \u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e$f1\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e$f2\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"pl-k\"\u003e\u0026gt;\u0026gt;\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e$OUT_TXT\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e \\\n      \u003cspan class=\"pl-k\"\u003e||\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"pl-c1\"\u003eecho\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003eMissing: \u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e$f1\u003c/span\u003e or \u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e$f2\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\n  \u003cspan class=\"pl-k\"\u003edone\u003c/span\u003e\n\n\u003cspan class=\"pl-k\"\u003edone\u003c/span\u003e\n\n\u003cspan class=\"pl-c\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-c\"\u003e#\u003c/span\u003e 2) DCJ-based clustering with Pling (after selecting pairs below threshold)\u003c/span\u003e\npling align --containment_distance 0.3 --cores 8 --sourmash plasmid.txt \u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-smi\"\u003e$OUTDIR\u003c/span\u003e/clustering/pling_out\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\"\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\n\n\n\u003cspan class=\"pl-c\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-c\"\u003e#\u003c/span\u003e## 4.10 Miscellaneous \u0026amp; Reporting\u003c/span\u003e\n\n- SNP/Mash distance matrices and visualizations were \u003cspan class=\"pl-k\"\u003edone\u003c/span\u003e manually\n- In general, I have had good experience with bandage (cited \u003cspan class=\"pl-k\"\u003ein\u003c/span\u003e the preprint) to get assembly visualisations and ProkSee \u003cspan class=\"pl-k\"\u003efor\u003c/span\u003e visualisation of functional annotations.\n- Be careful when re-running assemblies and matching contigs previously annotated with MOB-Suite to the new assemblies (i.e., with regards to contig length etc.), as flye might change the contig-numbering when re-running again\n- Species identification was conducted externally via Pathogenwatch and/or PubMLST (see corresponding publication)\n\n---\n\n\u003cspan class=\"pl-c\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-c\"\u003e#\u003c/span\u003e# 5. Suggested Folder Structure\u003c/span\u003e\n\n\u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e`\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e`\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e`\u003c/span\u003etext\u003c/span\u003e\n\u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003eproject/\u003c/span\u003e\n\u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e├─ raw/                     \u003cspan class=\"pl-c\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-c\"\u003e#\u003c/span\u003e POD5/FAST5 or raw FASTQs\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\n\u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-c\"\u003e├─ demux/\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\n\u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-c\"\u003e├─ filtered_reads/          # post-trim/filter\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\n\u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-c\"\u003e├─ flye/                    # raw assemblies\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\n\u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-c\"\u003e├─ medaka/                  # polished assemblies\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\n\u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-c\"\u003e├─ mob/                     # plasmid reconstruction\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\n\u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-c\"\u003e├─ amr/                     # AMR gene tables\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\n\u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-c\"\u003e├─ clustering/             # plasmid clustering \u0026amp; distances\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\n\u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-c\"\u003e└─ reports/                 # summary tables \u0026amp; figures\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003chr\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"markdown-heading\" dir=\"auto\"\u003e\u003ch2 tabindex=\"-1\" class=\"heading-element\" dir=\"auto\"\u003e6. Software Checklist\u003c/h2\u003e\u003ca id=\"user-content-6-software-checklist\" class=\"anchor\" aria-label=\"Permalink: 6. Software Checklist\" href=\"#6-software-checklist\"\u003e\u003csvg class=\"octicon octicon-link\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" version=\"1.1\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\u003e\u003cpath d=\"m7.775 3.275 1.25-1.25a3.5 3.5 0 1 1 4.95 4.95l-2.5 2.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1-4.95 0 .751.751 0 0 1 .018-1.042.751.751 0 0 1 1.042-.018 1.998 1.998 0 0 0 2.83 0l2.5-2.5a2.002 2.002 0 0 0-2.83-2.83l-1.25 1.25a.751.751 0 0 1-1.042-.018.751.751 0 0 1-.018-1.042Zm-4.69 9.64a1.998 1.998 0 0 0 2.83 0l1.25-1.25a.751.751 0 0 1 1.042.018.751.751 0 0 1 .018 1.042l-1.25 1.25a3.5 3.5 0 1 1-4.95-4.95l2.5-2.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1 4.95 0 .751.751 0 0 1-.018 1.042.751.751 0 0 1-1.042.018 1.998 1.998 0 0 0-2.83 0l-2.5 2.5a1.998 1.998 0 0 0 0 2.83Z\"\u003e\u003c/path\u003e\u003c/svg\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cul dir=\"auto\"\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eDorado (v5.0)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003ePorechop (v0.2.3), NanoFilt (v2.8.0), Seqkit (v2.10.0)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eFlye (v2.9.5)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eMinimap2 (v2.2.9), Samtools (v1.16.1)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eMedaka (v2.0.1)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eMOB-suite (v3.1.8)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eAMRFinderPlus (v4.0.3)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eMash (v2.3), Pling (v1.0.1)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003c/article\u003e","loaded":true,"timedOut":false,"errorMessage":null,"headerInfo":{"toc":[{"level":1,"text":"Carbapenem-resistant Enterobacterales: Plasmid-clustering pipeline","anchor":"carbapenem-resistant-enterobacterales-plasmid-clustering-pipeline","htmlText":"Carbapenem-resistant Enterobacterales: Plasmid-clustering pipeline"},{"level":2,"text":"1. Goal \u0026 Scope","anchor":"1-goal--scope","htmlText":"1. Goal \u0026amp; Scope"},{"level":2,"text":"2. Workflow Overview","anchor":"2-workflow-overview","htmlText":"2. Workflow Overview"},{"level":2,"text":"3. Inputs","anchor":"3-inputs","htmlText":"3. Inputs"},{"level":2,"text":"4. Detailed Steps \u0026 Codes","anchor":"4-detailed-steps--codes","htmlText":"4. Detailed Steps \u0026amp; Codes"},{"level":3,"text":"4.1 Basecalling","anchor":"41-basecalling","htmlText":"4.1 Basecalling"},{"level":3,"text":"4.2 Demultiplexing","anchor":"42-demultiplexing","htmlText":"4.2 Demultiplexing"},{"level":3,"text":"4.3 Trimming \u0026 Filtering","anchor":"43-trimming--filtering","htmlText":"4.3 Trimming \u0026amp; Filtering"},{"level":3,"text":"4.4 Assembly","anchor":"44-assembly","htmlText":"4.4 Assembly"},{"level":3,"text":"4.5 Depth estimation and Polishing","anchor":"45-depth-estimation-and-polishing","htmlText":"4.5 Depth estimation and Polishing"},{"level":3,"text":"4.6 Plasmid Reconstruction \u0026 Typing","anchor":"46-plasmid-reconstruction--typing","htmlText":"4.6 Plasmid Reconstruction \u0026amp; Typing"},{"level":3,"text":"4.7 AMR Gene Detection","anchor":"47-amr-gene-detection","htmlText":"4.7 AMR Gene Detection"},{"level":3,"text":"4.8 Chromosomal SNP Analysis","anchor":"48-chromosomal-snp-analysis","htmlText":"4.8 Chromosomal SNP Analysis"},{"level":3,"text":"4.9 Plasmid Clustering / Distances","anchor":"49-plasmid-clustering--distances","htmlText":"4.9 Plasmid Clustering / Distances"},{"level":2,"text":"6. Software Checklist","anchor":"6-software-checklist","htmlText":"6. Software Checklist"}],"siteNavLoginPath":"/login?return_to=https%3A%2F%2Fgithub.com%2FElaSrbrn%2FCarbapenem-resistant-Enterobacterales-Plasmid-clustering-pipeline"}}],"overviewFilesProcessingTime":0,"copilotSWEAgentEnabled":false}},"codeViewLayoutRoute":{"repo":{"id":1026093388,"defaultBranch":"main","name":"Carbapenem-resistant-Enterobacterales-Plasmid-clustering-pipeline","ownerLogin":"ElaSrbrn","currentUserCanPush":false,"isFork":false,"isEmpty":false,"createdAt":"2025-07-25T09:45:59.000Z","ownerAvatar":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/150910191?v=4","public":true,"private":false,"isOrgOwned":false},"currentUser":null,"uploadToken":"eVst11a1hUxYgxnwccqonKGsqcXeSkbKXFtdHfTu5Lmf1fVsCJ_qCwnCLuBeT2mowLM1cwY__0ynFhmzfhPhlw","allShortcutsEnabled":false,"treeExpanded":true,"path":"/","symbolsExpanded":false,"refInfo":{"name":"main","listCacheKey":"v0:1753436760.379294","canEdit":false,"currentOid":"9103547f135227870a368446d6afdc87b194bb75"},"helpUrl":"https://docs.github.com","findFileWorkerPath":"/assets-cdn/worker/find-file-worker-4e5d7136862a2a48.js","findInFile